theorem interior_complement_eq_complement_closure {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X]
    (A : Set X) :
    interior ((Aᶜ) : Set X) = (closure (A : Set X))ᶜ := by
  -- Start from the known relation applied to the complement `Aᶜ`.
  have h :=
    closure_compl_eq_complement_interior (A := (Aᶜ : Set X))
  -- This gives `closure A = (interior (Aᶜ))ᶜ`.
  have h₁ : closure (A : Set X) = (interior ((Aᶜ) : Set X))ᶜ := by
    simpa [Set.compl_compl] using h
  -- Taking complements of both sides yields the desired equality.
  have h₂ : (closure (A : Set X))ᶜ = interior ((Aᶜ) : Set X) := by
    have := congrArg Set.compl h₁
    simpa [Set.compl_compl] using this
  simpa [Set.compl_compl] using h₂.symm

theorem interior_compl_eq_complement_closure {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X]
    (A : Set X) :
    interior ((A : Set X)ᶜ) = (closure (A : Set X))ᶜ := by
  -- First, show `interior (Aᶜ) ⊆ (closure A)ᶜ`.
  have h₁ : interior ((A : Set X)ᶜ) ⊆ (closure (A : Set X))ᶜ := by
    intro x hx
    -- Assume, for a contradiction, that `x ∈ closure A`.
    by_contra hxCl
    have hxCl' : (x : X) ∈ closure (A : Set X) := by
      -- From `hxCl : x ∉ (closure A)ᶜ`, we obtain `x ∈ closure A`.
      by_cases hmem : (x : X) ∈ closure (A : Set X)
      · exact hmem
      · have : (x : X) ∈ (closure (A : Set X))ᶜ := by
          simpa [hmem] using (byCases_true (p := (x : X) ∈ closure (A : Set X)))
        exact (hxCl this).elim
    -- Use `mem_closure_iff` with the open set `interior (Aᶜ)`.
    have h_nonempty :
        (interior ((A : Set X)ᶜ) ∩ (A : Set X)).Nonempty := by
      have h_open : IsOpen (interior ((A : Set X)ᶜ)) := isOpen_interior
      exact (mem_closure_iff.1 hxCl') _ h_open hx
    -- But `interior (Aᶜ)` is contained in `Aᶜ`, so the intersection is empty.
    rcases h_nonempty with ⟨y, ⟨hyInt, hyA⟩⟩
    have : (y : X) ∈ ((A : Set X)ᶜ) := interior_subset hyInt
    exact this hyA
  -- Next, show `(closure A)ᶜ ⊆ interior (Aᶜ)`.
  have h₂ : (closure (A : Set X))ᶜ ⊆ interior ((A : Set X)ᶜ) := by
    -- The set `(closure A)ᶜ` is open and contained in `Aᶜ`,
    -- hence it is contained in `interior (Aᶜ)`.
    apply interior_maximal
    · -- `(closure A)ᶜ ⊆ Aᶜ`
      intro x hx
      by_contra hA
      have hxCl : (x : X) ∈ closure (A : Set X) := subset_closure hA
      exact hx hxCl
    · -- `(closure A)ᶜ` is open.
      have : IsOpen ((closure (A : Set X))ᶜ) :=
        (isClosed_closure : IsClosed (closure (A : Set X))).isOpen_compl
      simpa using this
  exact Set.Subset.antisymm h₁ h₂

theorem closure_union_eq_union_closure_left_of_isClosed {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X]
    {A B : Set X} (hA : IsClosed (A : Set X)) :
    closure ((A ∪ B) : Set X) = A ∪ closure (B : Set X) := by
  have h := closure_union_eq_union_closure (A := A) (B := B)
  simpa [hA.closure_eq] using h
